				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: duo suggestions Bard and Necro<a name="35208"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 17 04 6:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you want to control where the mob runs, and thus do NOT want to fear them, you do the pulling, and start chant kiting it.  When it gets down on health a little, snare it, sick the necro pet on it, and drag it wherever you like while the Necro starts applying their DoTs.  It might take a few tries before you get the aggro management down, but no biggie.  Have fear memmed in case things don't go as planned, and the necro gets too much aggro.  Or if he does, who cares.  He has 2.5 selos just like you, and the mob is snared.  /shrug.  Then he becomes the aggro-dragger.
<br />

<br />
This works real nice with Shammies and/or Druids too, hehe.</span></td>
