			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: duo suggestions Bard and Necro<a name="35429"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 19 04 12:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>To reiterate, bard/necro is possibly the best duo combo in the game.  My rl best friend is 65 necro, and we regularly do stuff that many full groups can't seem to handle.  We've successfully duoed adventures, and have even been relatively successful duoing hards (no wins, but a solid amount of kills, etc).
<br />

<br />
Outdoors, you can keep the 3 min speed song on the necro and just agro kite, cakewalk in any zone.  Even summoning mobs aren't too bad with that extra speed: necro can usually tap enough health back after summons, just takes a little extra mana.  HOH basement for example, we rip through those mobs quickly, AAs roll in.  When we get to the unsnarable mobs, I'll just kite for a few seconds before she starts laying on her dots, thus I keep agro for most of the battle, makin it easier on necro.
<br />

<br />
Dungeons are easy to farm, cuz 65 pet is an uber tank, necro can heal it, both of you can lay on dots, and bard can keep necro at full health just with marr, not to mention the mana regen.  And call of the muse adds to the necros dots.....it's almost unfair<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Really, there's almost nothing you can't do with that combo, you just need to start trying stuff.  If you fail, it'll probably only take a rethinking of your strategy, because there's not much we've ever failed on that we put our mind to.  Don't get carried away, you're aren't gonna take down Garudon in veksar, but you can take everything else (remains included).  
<br />

<br />
Both classes are just really versatile.  And I forgot that you're only 58, but still, there's a lot of solid things you can try.  I liked duoing the courtyard in pod, way more fun than solo and solid exp.  Also, the back wall (NE or near lever) in pov is fantastic exp kiting golems (spiders unsnarable, so you need to hold agro for a while if possible).  Droga and veksar are fun and easy farm spots.  HOH is the best once you hit 62 for exp.
<br />

<br />
Well, I'll post more after thinking about you're situation at 58, but what we did was mostly pod and pov, i'd recommend those two as starting points.
<br />

<br />
Elbereth, 65 bard (props to Carmina, 65 necro of the massive AAs <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-11.gif" border="0" alt="Cool" hspace="2" />), Cazic</span></td>
